Consider a scenario where resistor values are selected that do not exactly satisfy Eq. 5.23. Instead, the relationship among the resistors $R_{\mathrm{a}}, R_{\mathrm{b}}, R_{\mathrm{c}}$, and $R_{\mathrm{d}}$ is

$$
\frac{R_{\mathrm{a}}}{R_{\mathrm{b}}}=(1-\epsilon) \frac{R_{\mathrm{c}}}{R_{\mathrm{d}}}
$$

thus

$$
\begin{equation*}
R_{\mathrm{a}}=(1-\epsilon) R_{\mathrm{c}} \quad \text { and } \quad R_{\mathrm{b}}=R_{\mathrm{d}} \tag{5.32}
\end{equation*}
$$

or

$$
\begin{equation*}
R_{\mathrm{d}}=(1-\epsilon) R_{\mathrm{b}} \quad \text { and } \quad R_{\mathrm{a}}=R_{\mathrm{c}} \tag{5.33}
\end{equation*}
$$

